# debug_overlay.tas — F3-style debug overlay regression.
#
# Purpose: exercise the H-key toggle and confirm the overlay actually
# renders (and only the overlay, not menu screens) by comparing the
# top-left corner of two dumps:
#   * baseline: --debug-overlay=on  + this TAS  → H toggles OFF (no overlay)
#   * overlay : (no flag)           + this TAS  → H toggles ON  (overlay)
#
# Same TAS, same camera state, the only difference is whether the F3 panel
# was painted in the top-left. The brightness delta over the top-left
# corner should be > 1.0/255 (the dark translucent rect alone gives ~6).
#
# Usage (from utils/swindowzig):
#   zig build native -Dexample=voxel
#   ./examples/voxel/tests/debug_overlay.sh
#
# Tick numbering is relative to the first post-loading tick.

# --- Capture mouse so subsequent looks register. ---
1 mouse_down left
2 mouse_up left

# --- Hold the camera still for a few ticks so the FPS sampler settles. ---
4 mouse_move 0 0
6 mouse_move 0 0
8 mouse_move 0 0

# --- Toggle the F3 debug overlay with H (function-keys ban rules out F3). ---
10 keydown H
11 keyup H

# --- Hold steady so --dump-frame lands on a stable view. ---
20 mouse_move 0 0
30 mouse_move 0 0
